fondant help most help full i need an easy recipe for making fondant for a birthday cake anyone got any recipes that dont include mashmellows or gelatin mix please help this one is super easy doesn't contain marshmallows or gelatin cup light corn syrup cup shortening teaspoon salt teaspoon clear vanilla extract pounds confectioners' sugar in a large bowl stir together the shortening and corn syrup mix in the salt and vanilla flavoring then gradually mix in the confectioners' sugar until it is a stiff dough if you are using a stand mixer use the dough hook attachment otherwise knead by hand if the dough is sticky knead in more confectioners' sugar until it is smooth store in an airtight container at room temperature or in the refrigerator to use roll out on a clean surface that has been dusted with confectioners' sugar until it is inch thick or thinner if you can drape over frosted and chilled cakes and smooth the sides down or cut into strips to make bows and other decorations Bread Japanese cuisine Marshmallow Ice cream Tea Puff pastry Cookie Confectionery Tofu Cake Sugar Pizza Cheese Bagel Chocolate Soft drink Mayonnaise Coffee Cuisine of Denmark Cuisine of Singapore Pottery Halva Tortilla Brewery Chili con carne Turkish Delight Rice pudding Sushi Pop-Tarts Cold Stone Creamery Mooncake Food preservation Breakfast German cuisine Flour Jewish cuisine Cuisine of the Philippines Milkshake Soap bubble Pancake Bengali cuisine Haggis Dim sum Glass Dairy Ramen Vanilla Ketchup Soap Cantonese cuisine Rum Pasta Sangr__a Cuisine of the Southern United States Turkish coffee Barbecue Cooking weights and measures XML Vinegar Plastic Cuisine of Malaysia Beer Dumpling Gatorade Pecan pie Alice B. Toklas brownie Corned beef Cookware and bakeware Sugarcane Gingerbread Polish cuisine Bulk vending Drill bit Gluten Knife Hot chocolate In-N-Out Burger Vegetarian cuisine Japanese tea ceremony Hamster Milk Paneer Soul food Apple Brewing Diseases of the honeybee Chowder Toffee Cinnamon 